for 1kg potatoes (3 massive):
- 12g (10 small cloves) garlic
- 16g (two) spring onions, chopped
- 2 tsp toasted sesame seeds

[ both spice mixes ]
- 2.5g salt
- 5g (1 tsp) granulated sugar
- 6.5g chicken bullion

[ western spice mix ]
- 3g (two sprigs) rosemary, finely chopped
- 0.5g black pepper
- 0.5g white pepper

[ chinese spice mix ]
- 5g (2.5 tsp) sichuan peppercorn
- 2.7g (1 tsp) white peppercorns
- 1.8g (1 tsp) fennel seeds
- 1 star anise pod (optional)
- toasted in wok for 2 mins
- grind in mortar and pestle

[ jap spice mix ]
- 2g togarashi chilli powder
- 1 ground niboshi (dried anchovy)
- 2g furikake

- chop potato into 2cm cubes
- boil for 5 mins until just tender and knife goes in easy
  - still needs to survive frying
- leave tatos on drying rack to dry
- get high temp oil shimmering in pan (180°C)
- stir fry about 4 mins until brown spots on potatoes (about 4 mins)
- clear a space in the centre of the pan and add garlic, spring onions, sesame seeds, and spice mix. Stir fry for 15 seconds
- toss everything for another 15 seconds
- season with more salt as required
